her. Contributors to this book outline the history of the Vancouver network, its relationship with local government and other organizations in the region, the programs and activities offered, and the experiences of participants. While globalization and migration create fragmented and disconnected societies in modern urban cities, this timely study demonstrates that place-based community organizations can provide an antidote.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aFrancis, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHulchanski, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauer, Sean R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauer, Sean R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLauer, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOno, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiaño-Alcalá, Pilar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidtke, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStebner, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYan, Miu Chung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYan, Miu Chung, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486583840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774865838423Coveruhttps://www.de